{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Job Decries His Comforters"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then Job answered:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“I have heard many things like these; miserable comforters are you all."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Is there no end to your long-winded speeches? What provokes you to continue testifying?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I could also speak like youif you were in my place; I could heap up words against you and shake my head at you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But I would encourage you with my mouth, and the consolation of my lips would bring relief."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Even if I speak, my pain is not relieved, and if I hold back, how will it go away?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Surely He has now exhausted me; You have devastated all my family."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You have bound me, and it has become a witness; my frailty rises up and testifies against me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "His anger has torn me and opposed me; He gnashes His teeth at me.\nMy adversary pierces me with His eyes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They open their mouths against me and strike my cheeks with contempt;\nthey join together against me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "God has delivered me to unjust men; He has thrown me to the clutches of the wicked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I was at ease, but He shattered me; He seized me by the neck and crushed me. He has set me up as His target;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "His archers surround me. He pierces my kidneys without mercy and spills my gall on the ground."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He breaks me with wound upon wound; He rushes me like a mighty warrior."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I have sewn sackcloth over my skin; I have buried my horn in the dust."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My face is red with weeping, and deep shadows ring my eyes;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "yet my hands are free of violence and my prayer is pure."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "O earth, do not cover my blood; may my cry for help never be laid to rest."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Even now my witness is in heaven, and my advocate is on high."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My friends are my scoffersas my eyes pour out tears to God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Oh, that a man might plead with Godas he pleads with his neighbor!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For when only a few years are pastI will go the way of no return."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}